'''Cesare Zoppetti''' (1876-1940) was an Italian [[stage actor|stage]] and [[film actor]]. Zoppetti was a prolific film actor of the 1930s, appearing in nearly fifty productions between 1930 and his death in 1940 including the comedy ''[[What Scoundrels Men Are!]]'' (1932).<ref>Landy p.85-86</ref>

